##Home Isolation for 12 days, Wuhan Pneumonia, I think I beat it

Micro signal

Function description, Don Ma does not sleep

First Click on the blue above to follow me oh ~ 

Since I first developed symptoms on January 22, and today is the 12th day, two days ago, I started to reduce my fever by myself, and the frequency of my cough has dropped dramatically, counting today, I have had a fever drop for 3 days, my temperature has been around 36.5 all the time, there is no recurrence, at this point, I think I've beaten the virus.

The first six days of the case see suspected Wuhan Pneumonia, home isolation of the sixth day

The last article ended on the sixth day when I went to the community hospital for a blood test. Although the doctor told me to go back to quarantine myself, since my blood condition was not good, I was advised to go to the hospital for a CT scan.

The next day, the CT results came back, showing multiple plaques of infection in the lower lobes of both lungs

The doctor said I was a suspect, but since my symptoms weren't severe, he prescribed Moxifloxacin and told me to buy my own Oseltamivir and remain in isolation at home.

And on that night, a meal of dumplings made me suddenly realize that I had no sense of taste. Dumplings and vinegar are as plain as boiled water. When I think back to the situation of eating these days, I should have started to lose my sense of taste on the third or fourth day, i was so focused on the fever, the cough, the change in symptoms, that I ignored it.

That day, the cough began to get worse.

For the next two days, on the 29th and 30th, body temperature fluctuated between 37.5 and 38.2, cough remained severe, no sense of taste, and slight diarrhea.

GAMEÂ OVER ?

Everything took a turn on January 31st.

When I woke up in the morning, I felt a sense of relief in my chest.

In the past, except for the first 2 days with symptoms to feel chest tightness, other than the other time did not feel obvious, now look, may be a habit?

So now the relief in your chest is palpable, and your temperature is 36.6 and you don't feel the need to cough at all.

I mean, am I cured?

Yes, today, after two more days of observation, I am sure that I have recovered, my cough has decreased, and my sense of taste is slowly coming back.

The pneumonia virus. I beat you!

Here's how my symptoms changed. Click to enlarge

I'm not a doctor or a nurse, and I don't have a doctor or a friend to talk to, so I do it all on my own.

And from my results, for the ordinary suspected mild patients, is completely able to heal at home isolation, but there is a process.

The process of going from light to heavy to light and back to light, and finally to vanishing, is like climbing a mountain.

For example, my body temperature peaked at 39 and then dropped. For example, my cough never got much worse until it finally decreased.

So if you're home in quarantine with a mild case, don't panic if your symptoms are getting worse. Maybe you're just climbing a hill and will come down when you get to the top.

Just stay alert for persistent high fever and trouble breathing.

Postscript

For patients with mild illness, how home isolation, I would like to say a few I think important, I hope to help you.

1. First of all, for the occurrence of symptoms, suspected of their infection friends, can first go to "Yihe Health" and "Zhuozheng medical" 2 public number platform online consultation.

2. According to the National Health Commission issued a new case of pneumonia confirmation procedures notice, and in line with the following, can be judged as new suspected cases of pneumonia.

(a) a history of travel or residence in Wuhan in the two weeks prior to the onset of illness;

B. Or within 14 days before the onset of exposure from Wuhan fever with respiratory symptoms in patients, or have aggregated onset.

C. Fever with imaging features of pneumonia.

D. In the early stages of the disease, the white blood cell count is either normal or reduced, or the lymphocyte count is reduced.

3. At present, there is no effective drug to treat the pneumonia virus, rely on their own immune system, for no basic diseases, no sustained high fever, breathing difficulties of mild patients, self-isolation is the best way.

It is easy to cross-infection if you go to hospital with mild illness, and the possibility of admission is not great. I would have stayed at home if it hadn't been for the first time that I had gone out to the hospital on the sixth day of my fever, after the community hospital had started to accept fever patients.

4. Similarly, for people with mild illness, I don't recommend going to the hospital and waiting in line for a nucleic acid test. We want to get tested because we need a sense of certainty? If you have a mild case, your doctor will still recommend that you stay at home under quarantine. There is no change in our treatment before and after the test. Instead, you have to go to the hospital at the risk of cross-infection.

5. Do not panic, fear of infection on their own to take drugs, to understand that many of the side effects of drugs may be chest tightness, panic, dizziness, diarrhea, so your symptoms may also be emotional + drug side effects.

6. As long as the way of droplet transmission can be avoided by wearing a mask, and the way of contact infection, often overlooked, that is, hand hygiene.

Your hands will come in contact with masks, cell phones, doorknobs, and more public goods if you go out shopping, and your hands will be a source of infection and cross-pollinate with the things you come in contact with. If you don't wash your hands properly and rub your eyes, nose and mouth with your hands, you'll get an infection.

So always remember to wash your hands with soap and water, do not touch your mouth and nose with your hands, more important than wearing a mask.

Kill. For suspected patients in isolation at home, wear a mask, try to ensure patients alone in a room, if not necessary, can not leave the room, maintain ventilation, all use items as far as possible to maintain dedicated. If there is a public use area, the patient after use disinfection for family use.

For example, in my home, because there is only one bathroom, my practice is toilet roll separate use, toilet seat, flush button, faucet switch after use when disinfection. If I have a bath in the bathroom, then wait until the bathroom is completely dry, teammates go in to use, to avoid carrying the virus of Water Vapor floating in the air to be inhaled.

8. Keeping a relaxed mood is good for getting your immune system into shape and fighting off illness. For those who are stressed, worried, anxious, out of control, and unable to cope, check out the tips in my last article or ask a professional for help.
Wuhan Mental Health Centre Psychological Hotline 027-85844666(9:00-21:00)
Or download the simple psychology APP and click on the free hotline at the front page (18:00-24:00)
